# The Bashkir braille code was created by Makarim Tukhvatshin in the
# early 60's. There is no official documentation on the braille code
# that we know of.

# Bashkir braille is largely the same as Russian braille
include ru-litbrl.ctb


# The Bashkir alphabet has 9 letters that are not in the Russian
# alphabet, namely Ó, Óš, Ò , Ò, Òª, Ò, Òº, Ò® and Ò¢. Like in ru-chardefs.cti, the
# following definitions have dot 9 set to make them distinguishable
# from the Latin letters.
uppercase \x04D8 34579   CYRILLIC LETTER ÃŠ Ó
uppercase \x04E8 12679   CYRILLIC LETTER Ãž Óš
uppercase \x04A0 14679   CYRILLIC LETTER q Ò 
uppercase \x0492 1245679 CYRILLIC LETTER É£ Ò
uppercase \x04AA 3479    CYRILLIC LETTER Îž Òª
uppercase \x0498 34679   CYRILLIC LETTER Ã° Ò
uppercase \x04BA 123679  CYRILLIC LETTER h Òº
uppercase \x04AE 1345679 CYRILLIC LETTER y Ò®
uppercase \x04A2 145679  CYRILLIC LETTER Å Ò¢
